<>20/01/2004
       
Israeli warplanes launch an air strike on southern Lebanon, a day after Hezbollah militants killed an Israeli soldier.
Rescuers call off the hunt for survivors of a cargo ship that capsized in a fjord near Bergen, with 15 people still missing.
The defence secretary faces questions on claims night goggles might have prevented a helicopter crash in Iraq.
The drive to win round support for plans for student top-up fees is boosted by backing from an international think tank.
Transport Minister Kim Howells says the government "got quite a bit wrong" in its reforms of the railways.
